1. A decrease in the number of cumulative cases and discrepancies in the
difference between cumulative number of cases of the last and the current
WHO update is attributed to the discarding of cases.
2. Includes cases who are "discharged" or "recovered" as reported by the
national public health authorities.
3. National public health authorities report to WHO on the areas in which
local chain(s) of transmission is/are occurring. These areas are provided
on the list of Affected Areas.
4. One death attributed to Hong Kong SAR China occurred in a case medically
transferred from Viet Nam.
[B] The list of affected areas can be accessed at:
