[2]
Date: 26 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Hong Kong - Department of Health [edited]
<http://www.info.gov.hk/dh/new/index.htm>

Situation report on atypical pneumonia 26 Apr 2003
--------------------------------------------------
The following is jointly issued by the Department of Health and the
Hospital Authority:
As of 1 PM 26 Apr 2003, there are an additional 17 patients confirmed to
have atypical pneumonia following admission to public hospitals earlier.
They include 3 health care workers (one from Caritas Medical Centre, one
from Tai Po Hospital, and one from Alice Ho Miu Ling Nethersole Hospital).
The remaining 14 are other patients and contacts of patients with atypical
pneumonia.
A total of 632 patients have recovered from atypical pneumonia and have
been discharged from public hospitals. Of them, 18 were discharged today.
There are also 129 recovering patients who are in convalescence and
preparation for discharge. 101 patients are receiving treatment in
intensive care units.
6 patients died in Caritas Medical Centre (CMC), Princess Margaret Hospital
(PMH), Tuen Mun Hospital (TMH), and United Christian Hospital (UCH). This
brought to 121 the total number of deaths relating to atypical pneumonia.
The deceased are aged from 28 to 70 and include one woman and 5 men. [4
were otherwise healthy individuals under the age of 50 years - Mod.MPP]
The cumulative figure for patients who have been admitted to public
hospitals with atypical pneumonia since 12 Mar 2003 is as follows:
Cumulative no. cases / total no. discharged patients / total no. deaths*
Health care workers of hospitals/clinics and medical students: 345 / 140 / ?
Patients, family members & visitors: 1182 / 492 / ?
Total: 1527 ** / 632 / 121
Suspected cases: 26
* Most of the deaths occurred in individuals who have a history of chronic
diseases, or were patients who sought treatment at a relatively late stage
of infection.
** There are 129 recovering patients in convalescence.
