Date: 26 Apr 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Health Canada 25 Apr 2003 (accessed 26 Apr 2003) [edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/english/protection/warnings/sars/update39.html>

Update 39 - SARS 25 Apr 2003 6:00 PM
------------------------------------
As of 25 Apr 2003, Health Canada has received reports of 341 probable or
suspect cases of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) in Canada. There
have been 18 deaths in Canada. To date, transmission has been limited to
specific transmission settings such as households, hospitals and specific
community settings. The information contained in this update is based on
the information available to Health Canada at this time.
The details of the cases to date are as follows:
Ontario is reporting 138 probable and 127 suspect cases.
British Columbia is reporting 4 probable and 60 suspect cases.
New Brunswick is reporting 2 suspect cases.
Saskatchewan is reporting 1 suspect case.
Alberta is reporting 5 suspect cases.
Prince Edward Island is reporting 4 suspect cases.
Total no. of probables discharged: 75
Total no. of probables recovering at home: 2
Total no. of suspects discharged: 85
Total no. of suspects recovering at home: 69
These numbers are accurate as of 1:00 PM EDST 25 Apr 2003.
[The most recent epidemiological analysis of reported SARS cases in Canada
is available through 24 Apr 2003 and can be accessed at:
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/sars-sras/eu-ae/sars20030424_e.html>.
In the epidemic curve presented in that update, the date of onset of the
most recent case reported is 14 Apr 2003, or 12 days ago. The additional
reports of new cases may not reflect cases with more recent dates of onset,
but rather may reflect later identification of cases. Readers are reminded
that the case definition for probable case of SARS is one of exclusion, so
that other causes of a severe acute respiratory illness with an atypical
pneumonia may be ruled out by physicians before a case is reported as a
suspect or probable case. (see
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/sars-sras/sarscasedef-0317_e.html> for
the case definitions used in Canada). - Mod.MPP]
